The Old St. Johns Gun Shop - 13.78 Acres with Endless Potential! Two adjoining parcels combine to offer nearly 14 acres of opportunity just 10.5 miles from St. Johns-8 miles of smooth pavement and only 2 miles of county-maintained gravel road. This longtime family property once grew acres of corn and includes a pond that could be restored to hold water again. It borders State Trust Land, offering added privacy, open space, and excellent hunting opportunities right out your back door. One parcel features striking rock ledges and a high point where you can glimpse the waters of Lyman Lake. A manufactured home with added rooms and the original gun shop (in need of repair) remain on the land, along with a water well, electric power, and a county-approved septic system. Once home to a small shooting range and several dwellings (now removed), this versatile property invites new lifewhether as a private retreat, business revival, or investment for future growth. Amazing Anasazi petroglyphs are abundant in the area allowing for hours of exploration. Seller financing available! Just 30% down and $884.64 per month makes this a rare chance to own a piece of family history with flexible terms and endless potential.

Enjoy mountain living in this spacious 2011 manufactured home on .42 acres. With 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, this home is designed with comfort and functionality. Inside you'll find Updated paint, New flooring in all bedrooms, a large primary suite with large bathroom and a large kitchen with center island and pantry. Outside, the spacious, fenced backyard offers a versatile space for pets, entertaining, and outdoor gear. An added storage shed offers convenient space for storing additional items. This versatile property works beautifully as a full-time residence or an affordable weekend getaway.

Discover this fantastic canvas for your future home! Now available for sale is a wonderful 1.03-acre parcel with essential city utilities: water, power, and sewer. Nestled at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac, this level vacant lot offers a country setting without a homeowner's association. Imagine building your dream residence in an area that combines the tranquility of rural life with the convenience of nearby city amenities. Located within easy access to great schools, parks, and shopping, this lot provides the ideal foundation for constructing a house tailored to your personal tastes and needs. Want to grow your own food? There is plenty of space for a garden. Bring your architect and visions of home sweet home. It's a blank slate awaiting your creative touch. Whether you're envisioning a cozy bungalow or a sprawling estate, the possibilities are as expansive as the clear Arizona sky. Grab this opportunity to transform this peaceful plot into your new haven.

Escape into your own slice of history with this irresistibly charming home! Tucked behind a fully fenced yard for privacy, this gem features fresh paint, updated flooring, windows and a beautiful refreshed kitchen. Cozy up with the adorable pellet stove, or choose propane or electric heat. Enjoy a spacious living room, generous bedrooms including 1 with an exterior door for versatility and a shower in the bathroom that includes bluetooth accessibility. A dedicated dining area gives the home a warm, open feel. There are hardwood floors underneath current laminate flooring, if you desire to restore the historic nature of the home. Enjoy extra attic storage-plus a potential bonus room in attic. The backyard provides raised garden beds. Built-in irrigation makes it convenient to water the lawn & flower beds that surround the house. Multiple storage sheds, a workshop with electricity and a chicken coop to complete your homestead. Mature, producing fruit trees add to the property's magic along with a greenhouse. In addition to city water, an existing well is on site (not currently in use and should be inspected), adding even more potential to this modern-country retreat. Mail is delivered straight to your mailbox out front!

This 4 bed/2 bath site-built home is located in a great neighborhood and offers a solid, well-built foundation for comfortable living. Featuring a durable metal roof and fresh interior paint, the home is move-in ready yet full of potential for your personal touch. A large concrete pad has already been poured along the entire length of the back of the home-perfect for a future addition, covered patio, or outdoor living area. The spacious yard provides plenty of room for play, gardening, or entertaining. With its great bones and excellent location, this property is ready for your ideas and offers a wonderful opportunity to expand and make it your own.
